# Data Log — India Hospital Chains FY25 Benchmarking
All figures FY25 (Apr 2024–Mar 2025) unless noted. C = Confirmed (company-reported), E = Estimate/derived, R = Research-firm estimate.

## APOLLO HOSPITALS ENTERPRISE LTD (consolidated, incl. HealthCo/pharmacy/AHLL)
- FY25 Consolidated revenue: Rs 21,794 Cr (+14% YoY) — C [company press release, 30 May 2025]
- Healthcare Services (hospitals) revenue: Rs 11,147 Cr (+13% YoY, crossed Rs 10,000 Cr first time) — C
- FY25 Consolidated EBITDA: Rs 3,022 Cr (+26% YoY) — C
- Healthcare Services EBITDA: Rs 2,701 Cr (+15% YoY); HCS EBITDA margin: 24.2% — C
- Consolidated EBITDA margin (blended, incl. pharmacy/HealthCo): ~13.9% (3,022/21,794) — E (derived)
- FY25 Consolidated PAT: Rs 1,446 Cr (+61% YoY) — C
- Occupancy: ~67-68% full-year (Q4 67%, FY25 avg ~68% per HSIE) — C/E blend
- ARPOB: ~Rs 59,000-60,000/day full-year average (Q1 FY25 Rs 59,073; regional Q4 prints ranged Rs 48k-78k) — C (Q-level), E (FY avg)
- Payor mix: most recent disclosed full split is FY24 — 39% cash, 43% insurance, ~7% international, balance govt/corporate. FY25 directional commentary: insurance share targeted higher, no new clean full split disclosed in FY25 filings reviewed — E (using FY24 base, flagged as last disclosed full split)
- Hospital segment is ~51% of consolidated revenue (11,147/21,794); HealthCo (pharmacy/digital) ~42%, AHLL ~7%

## FORTIS HEALTHCARE LTD (consolidated, incl. Agilus Diagnostics)
- FY25 Consolidated revenue: Rs 7,782.75 Cr (vs Rs 6,892.92 Cr FY24, +12.9% YoY) — C [Medical Buyer, citing company filing]
- FY25 Consolidated operating EBITDA: Rs 1,588 Cr (+25.3% YoY); margin 20.4% (vs 18.4% FY24) — C
- Hospital business EBITDA margin: 20.5% (vs 18.6% FY24); Hospital EBITDA: Rs 1,339 Cr — C
- Hospital business = ~84% of consolidated revenue and EBITDA — C
- Occupancy: 69% FY25 (up from 65% FY24) — C
- ARPOB: ~Rs 2.42 Cr/bed/annum (~Rs 66,300/day) FY25, vs Rs 2.22 Cr FY24 (+9%) — C
- International patient revenue: ~8% of hospital revenue (Q3 FY25) — C
- CGHS (govt scheme) revenue: ~4% of total revenue (FY24 base, company actively working to reduce this share due to low realization) — C (FY24), directionally flat/declining in FY25
- Payer mix: company discloses cash/TPA-insurance/international/CGHS buckets qualitatively but not a precise FY25 numeric split in sources reviewed — E for precise %; CGHS ~4% is the one hard number found

