## NARAYANA HRUDAYALAYA LTD (Narayana Health) — India + Cayman Islands
- FY25 Revenue: Rs 5,483 Cr / Rs 54,830 Mn (+9.3% YoY) — C [stock analyst note citing filings]
- FY25 India revenue: Rs 4,349.9 Cr (+11.3% YoY) — C
- FY25 Cayman Islands revenue: Rs 379.7 Cr (+50.2% YoY) — C
- FY25 EBITDA: Rs 1,276.4 Cr / Rs 12,764 Mn (+10.8% YoY); margin 23.3% — C
- FY25 PAT: Rs 798.2 Cr (+1.1% YoY) — C
- Cayman EBITDA margin: ~44% (Rs 166.3 Cr EBITDA / Rs 379.7 Cr revenue) — C — structurally much higher margin than India business (insurance/self-pay heavy, no govt scheme exposure)
- India ARPOB: ~Rs 46,301/day (+11% YoY) — C
- Occupancy: ~60-65% (management guidance, FY25) — E (best public estimate, not precisely disclosed)
- Payer mix: not cleanly disclosed in numeric split; NH's model is historically skewed toward affordable/self-pay and standardized-package insurance (low-cost high-volume cardiac model), with growing focus on "increasing payor mix" per management commentary — E (qualitative, directional only)

## INDUSTRY CONTEXT
- India health insurance market size: ~USD 157.6 Bn (2025), projected USD 322.1 Bn by 2034, CAGR 8.27% (2026-34) — R [IMARC]
- Alt. GWP-based sizing: USD 15.06 Bn (2024) → CAGR 20.9% (2025-30) — R [Grand View Research] — NOTE: divergent market-sizing methodologies across research firms; flagged as estimate range, not single confirmed figure
- Total health insurance premiums FY25: Rs 1,18,688 Cr (~9.1% YoY growth per Business Standard, citing IRDAI) — C
- Standalone health insurers FY26 growth guidance: 20-21% — R (industry guidance)
- Insurance penetration (overall insurance, life+non-life): 3.7% of GDP FY25 — C [IRDAI/IBEF]
- Health insurance coverage: ~36% of population (FY25) vs ~17% (FY12) — R (brokerage estimate, directional)
- PM-JAY (Ayushman Bharat) cards issued: 34.5+ Cr — C [NHA data via Business Today]
- PM-JAY empanelled hospitals: 32,000+ total, ~13,000 private — C
- Private hospital empanelment growth FY25: +12% YoY — C
- BUT: monthly empanelment pace collapsed — 316/month avg in 2024 → 111/month avg in early 2025 (only 20 new empanelments in May 2025) — C [NHA data via Medical Dialogues] — cited reason: package rates considered too low to cover costs, esp. tertiary/complex care
- India hospital sector EBITDA margins: stabilized at 21-22% (sector avg, FY25) — R [CareEdge Ratings]
- Sector net leverage: improved from ~5.0x (FY19) to ~1.4x (FY25) — R [CareEdge]
- Hospital sector growth outlook: 11-12% CAGR forward, 16-18% revenue growth guided for FY26 specifically — R [CareEdge/ICRA]
- Avg daily revenue per bed across top listed hospitals: Rs 49,304 FY25 (+23% YoY) — R [sector-wide tracker, Whalesbook/data aggregator — treat as directional, not primary-sourced]
- India hospital market size: USD 193.4 Bn (2025) — R [IMARC]

